Installation of kali linux in VMware workstation
1. Download ISO file from Kali Linux Page
2. Open VMware & select the option Create New Virtual Machine
3. Insert ISO File
    -In Install from choose Installer disc file(iso) browser through and select ISO file
    Than select Next>
4. Give the virtual machine name and than select next
5. Set maximum disk size(GB) and split virtual disk into multiple files. Than click next
6. Click Finish 

Go back to VMware Workstation to insall kali linux
1. click on Paly virtual machine
2. Click on graphical install (Press ctrl + atl to come back to windows)
3. Select language, country, hostname and password. Click Continue
4. Finish the installation. Installation is competed, click on continue





